# Utils

Pure helper functions (no React, no side effects) that are used in more than one place belong in `src/lib/utils/` (one file per helper or small domain). Domain-specific helpers that map or derive from app types (e.g. `Plan`) are utils, not component-local logic.

- Keep functions pure: same inputs → same outputs, no I/O.
- Import types from the concrete constants file (e.g. `@/lib/constants/plans`) as needed.
- Add new helpers as new files under `src/lib/utils/`; do not use a barrel index (see no-barrel-files rule).
- Constants live in `src/lib/constants/` (breakpoints, landing, plans, subscription, support). Import directly from the file (e.g. `@/lib/constants/support`). No barrel index.
